    {
      "id": "a1629e754e94bf92705514d47062cf9ba30c5ac2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2014-05-14 05:53:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nI feel like test 400a in sanity always failing on developer systems is bad.\nThis is something people are supposedly run all the time. The failure also has pretty long output which is annoying.\n\nWe should at least check that /usr/include/lustre is there and skip the test if not. I kind of dislike how it ignores other potential package locations, but inventing a special autodetect logic just for this is overkill, so just fixed locations is probably ok as long as we make sure it's there.\n\nIt would not be bad to test that $CC actually is there and works too before drawing any conclusions.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
